Hepatoma cell lysates were applied onto the four columns connected in series: three upper columns contained 1mL of His-binding (or rabbit IgG sepharose)resin and one lower column contained 1mL of His-K protein resin. After running the load, columns were washed and proteins were eluted from resin. Proteins eluted from the columns were concentrated by ultrafiltration. Proteins eluted individually from the third and the bottom columns were digested and then analyzed separately by LC-ESI-MSMS/ MS.
